Examples

Science Advances SI Figure 16

Figure 16 showcases the experimental testing of RNA strand displacement between I1 and a ctRSD gate with a DNA reporter assay.

Some Functionalities used:

  • globally changing rates with global_rate_constants

  • changing initial condtions/indiviudal rates within molecular_species

  • launching simulation using simulate

  • pulling out desired output concentrations using output_concentration

Science Advances SI Figure 31B

Figure 31B in the SI shows the influence of total template concentration and T7 RNAP concentration on transcriptional load. In terms, of the simulator, this example presents the need to be able to test different transcription rates in order to know which would fit best with one’s experimental design. The simulator uses the transcription_calibration function to fill this need.

Note:

Click here for full features of the transcription_calibration function.

Some Functionalities used:

  • globally changing rates with global_rate_constants

  • changing initial condtions/indiviudal rates within molecular_species

  • launching simulation using simulate

  • pulling out desired output concentrations using output_concentration

  • calibration transcription rates using transcription_calibration
